snippet.textDisplay: Coke Studio used to be known for its strong focus on the studio experience, soulful lyrics with Sufi themes, and an emphasis on vocal performance. Now, it feels more like a movie set. While I appreciate the artistry, I'm not here for the visuals. I remember many songs from the older seasons, but very few from the newer ones. So far, "Jhol" is the only recent song I've enjoyed enough to listen to multiple times. However, I found "Turri Jandi" to be very forgettable; I couldn't even finish listening to it once.
snippet.textOriginal: Coke Studio used to be known for its strong focus on the studio experience, soulful lyrics with Sufi themes, and an emphasis on vocal performance. Now, it feels more like a movie set. While I appreciate the artistry, I'm not here for the visuals. I remember many songs from the older seasons, but very few from the newer ones. So far, "Jhol" is the only recent song I've enjoyed enough to listen to multiple times. However, I found "Turri Jandi" to be very forgettable; I couldn't even finish listening to it once.
